@NODE INSTALL
@TITLE "05 Installation"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                     @{I} "Only AMIGA makes it possible."@{UI}
                        
                           @{B}TheBoss Installation@{UB}

  TheBoss is very easy install. Just use one of these simple methods.

  1. Use the included install program. Click on the Install icon, and
     all required files are automatically copied to the directory you
     specified.

     You must have the Installer utility to use this option. The
     current Installer utility may be found at Aminet/util/misc/
     Installer-43.3.lha.

  2. Do a manual installation copying the necessary files yourself.

     Create a new directory wherever you want and naming it whatever
     you want.

     Copy the following files to that directory.

     * TheBoss  * ThePrefs  * TheGuide French/English * Catalogs Dir

     Next, copy either the MWB or Newicons from their respective
     icon archive directory to TheBoss directory.

     That is all the files that need to be copied to complete manual
     installation.

  TheBoss does not require any assgnments to be made in either the
  startup-sequence or user-startup. What a pleasant surprise!    

  After installation is completed, you may start TheBoss Preferences
  for initial configuration.

  Any periodic TheBoss updates will not require re-installation. Simply
  copy the new version files to the TheBoss directory overwriting the
  previous installation. Since all files are located in the programdir,
  installation and removal are fast and easy.

@ENDNODE

