@NODE MAINWINDOW
@TITLE "08 The Main Preferences Window"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                     @{B}The Main Preferences Window@{UB}

  The main Preferences window is the first TheBoss experience unless
  Preferences is skipped after installation. Do not skip the initial
  configuration with the Preferences utility. It is important. It
  may contribute directly to the initial impression received from
  TheBoss.

  The main Preferences window has five gadgets: Screenmode, Screen
  Font, Button Font, Options and Palette. This five gadgets are each
  treated separately.

  Clicking any of the five gadgets opens the appropriate window
  corresponding to the selected gadget.

  Additionally, there are two gadgets to Save or Cancel the Preferences
  selections.

  If Cancel is selected, Preferences exits. No Preference settings
  are saved.

  If Save is selected, Preferences writes TheBoss.pref file to the
  programdir. This contains all the selected Preference settings. All
  further configuration operations write to this file. It can be fairly
  stated that this file is TheBoss. It contains all the data and
  configuration information required to make TheBoss the system boss.

                              @{B}Comments@{UB}

  When Preferences is first run, a requestor pops open stating:
  Configuration File Not Found. This is normal. Preferences creates
  the Configuration file. Just click Okay and continue.

  If TheBoss is started without initial Preferences configuration, all 
  default settings are used.

@ENDNODE
 
