@NODE SCREENMODE
@TITLE "09 The Screen Mode Selections"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN} @{" Author " LINK AUTHOR}

                       @{B}The Screen Mode Selections@{UB}

  TheBoss runs on any public or custom screen. Or if none is selected,
  then on its own screen.

  The Screen Mode selections window two options for screen type, text
  string gadget to enter screen name and the Screen Mode selector
  gadget.

  1. The Use Default Public Screen is enabled for the Workbench screen.
     The text string gadget indicates Workbench. This is the default.

  2. The Use Custom Public Screen enabled allows selection of an
     alernative public screen. The screen name must be entered in
     the text string gadget. If no name is entered, TheBoss will open
     its own screen. If a name is entered which does not exist in the
     opened public screen list, TheBoss will open a new public screen
     using the selected name (i.e., Multiview PUBSCREEN TheBossScreen).

  3. The Screen Mode gadget opens the Screen Mode requestor window.
     Select the screen resolution desired. All the usual screen modes
     the usual screen modes are supported. Actual supported screen 
     resolutions vary depending on OCS/ECS/AGA systems.

                              @{B}Comments@{UB}

  TheBoss has been tested on the Picasso IV with Picasso 96 drivers
  with no problems. TheBoss has not been tested on older generation
  GFX boards (such as the Retina II). TheBoss should be compatiable
  with all current GFX boards. Kindly contact the Author if any
  problems are encountered.

@ENDNODE

   ********************************************************************

    10                   - BEGIN NODE SCREENFONT -

