@NODE SCREENFONT
@TITLE "10 Screen Font Selection "
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                        @{B}Screen Font Selection@{UB}

  TheBoss has two options for the selection of the screen font: Use
  Default Font and Use Custom Font. Each option has a selection gadget.

  Use Default Font is TheBoss default. The default font is the system
  default screen font.

  Use Customs Font is the more appealing option. Click the font
  selector gadget to open the font selection window.

  Recommend selection of an 8-point font. Fonts smaller than 8-point
  are not supported.

  Click Okay or Cancel to exit to main window.

@ENDNODE
 
   ********************************************************************

    11                   - BEGIN NODE BUTTONFONT -

   ********************************************************************

@NODE BUTTONFONT
@TITLE "11 Button Font Selection"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                        @{B}Button Font Selection@{UB}

  TheBoss has two options for the selection of the screen font: Use
  Default Font and Use Custom Font. Each option has a selection gadget.
  
  Use Default Font is TheBoss default. The default font is the system
  default screen font.

  Use Customs Font is the more appealing option. Click the font
  selector gadget to open the font selection window.

  Recommend selection of an 8-point font. Fonts smaller than 8-point
  are not supported. The selected font is global. All buttons use
  the selected font.

  Click Okay or Cancel to exit to main window.

                              @{B}Comments@{UB}

  Font point size proportionately changes button size. Large point
  size fonts create large buttons. Recommend no more than 11/12 
  point font if a larger font size is desired. 

  Larger point fonts may be helpful to the visually impaired.

@ENDNODE

