@NODE OPTIONS
@TITLE "12 The Option Selections"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                        @{B}The Option Selections@{UB}

  TheBoss offers four global button options. The options are not button
  specific. Selected options apply to the entire configuration.
  1. TITLE BAR is the TheBoss default without initial preference
     configuraton. The Title Bar has the standard window gadgets. It
     does not have the vertical scroll bar and resize gadget. The Title
     Bar is the drag gadget. The Title Bar window may be dragged and
     positioned anywhere on the screen.

  2. BORDERLESS enabled creates a special button. Borderless buttons 
     have the attributes of a Title Bar button without the title bar.
     The Close gadget is upper left. The Drag gadget is upper right.
     These gadgets are 10 pixels wide. The space between the gadgets
     is an "active" button. The use is not restricted. It can be 
     designated as a Drawer, Executable or Script in the Configuration
     window. The best use is as an Executable button for the panel 
     label or name.

  3. DOUBLECLICK enabled requires a LMB or RMB doubleclick on all
     TheBoss functions. A single click is TheBoss default.

  4. EXIT REMEMBER enabled means that all opened window are remembered
     at "Quit" or "Exit". Exit Remember is useful. It means the usual
     open windows open at startup with the exact positions remembered.

                              @{B}Comments@{UB} 

  Only two options are mutually exclusive: Title Bar and Borderless.
  Only one may be selected and not both. The selected option is a
  matter of personal taste and fancy.

  Doubleclick emulates normal mouse button operation. The Single click
  default may result in a program running twice. Doubleclick is the
  the usual mouse button function mode. Remember that Doubleclick is 
  global and applies to all TheBoss functions.

  Borderless buttons with Exit Remember enabled are the preferred
  options. 

@ENDNODE

