@NODE MOUSE
@TITLE "14 The Mouse Buttons"
@{"  Main   " LINK MAIN}

                        @{B}The Mouse Buttons@{UB}

  TheBoss uses both mouse buttons for different functions.

  The LMB (for Left mouse button) is the "action" button. The LMB
  opens drawers or runs programs and scripts.

  The RMB (for Right mouse button) is the "configuration" button.
  If a window is active, clicking the RMB opens the Configuration
  window.

  All gadgets in the Configuration window respond to either LMB/RMB
  button clicks. There is no need to keep switching between mouse
  buttons. This feature simplifies and speeds the configuration process.

                              @{B}Comments@{UB}

  Using either the LMB or LMB consistently speeds up configuration.
  Switching between mouse buttons slows configuration down. Try to
  stick one favored mouse button only until it becomes automatic.
  
@ENDNODE
 
